A LEOPARD was seen walking around town yesterday morning. According to North West police, the leopard was spotted by a bus driver on the streets of Hartbeesfontein, near Klerksdorp. He immediately reported it to the nearest cop shop. Provincial police spokeswoman Captain Afjee Botma confirmed a bus driver claimed to have seen a leopard or wild cat. “The bus driver reported it to the police and the police reported it to the relevant authorities. Nature conservation officials are on their way,” she said. “We want to warn communities to be on the look-out and to be careful. They should not confront the animal but call the police.” Councillor Paki Mqikela said: “The police confirmed to me that the relevant authorities are on the look-out for the animal. “We appeal to the community to be careful. They should report any strange sounds.”